{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "These perspectives complement our observation of increased motivation and engagement among students for ChatGPT's accessibility in learning activities.",
    "The findings of the current study are also consistent with previous research (Ali et al., 2023; Habeb Al-Obaydi et al., 2023; Kim et al., 2023; Kohnke et al., 2023; Leunard et al., 2023; Niyozov et al., 2023; Tipayavaravan et al., 2023; Yan, 2023) which support the effectiveness of Chat-GPT in language learning and its potential to create an enhanced language learning experience and to revolutionize language pedagogy, although further investigation is needed to fully understand its impact and potential in various learning environments.",
    "Guo and Wang (2023) observed that ChatGPT offers more comprehensive feedback in EFL writing than human teachers, albeit with mixed teacher perceptions.",
    "Further supporting this, Hwang et al. (2023) demonstrated significant improvements in EFL writing through AI-Generated Sample Sentences (AI-SS) and AI-Writing Feedback (AI-WF), which resonates with our findings on ChatGPT's role in improving writing skills.",
    "The interactive and feedback-oriented nature of ChatGPT evidently aligns with these emerging pedagogical tools, suggesting a broader trend in the effective use of AI in language education."
  ],
